		"body": "This is a new feature, adding post-quantum resistant TLS key exchange to Joplin.\r\n\r\nReference this forum post for details: https://discourse.joplinapp.org/t/postquantum-safe/49540/1\r\n\r\nI tested `joplin-desktop` on Linux (NixOS) with a webdav sync target behind nginx, using the nginx option `ssl_ecdh_curve X25519MLKEM768;` to enforce post-quantum key exchange.\r\n\r\nI also did a wireshark capture and validated that X25519MLKEM768 is sent on the wire in a TLS ClientHello.",
